In [110]:
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller

# Perform seasonal differencing (12 months)
btc_month['box_diff_seasonal_12'] = btc_month['close_box'] - btc_month['close_box'].shift(12)

# Drop NaN values created by differencing
btc_month.dropna(subset=['box_diff_seasonal_12'], inplace=True)

# Perform Dickey-Fuller test
adf_test = adfuller(btc_month['box_diff_seasonal_12'])
p_value = adf_test[1]  # Extract p-value from test result

print("Dickey–Fuller test: p=%f" % p_value)

# Interpretation
if p_value < 0.05:
    print("The time series is stationary (reject the null hypothesis).")
else:
    print("The time series is not stationary (fail to reject the null hypothesis).")

Dickey–Fuller test: p=0.099522
The time series is not stationary (fail to reject the null hypothesis).

In [115]:
from itertools import product
from statsmodels.tsa.statespace.sarimax import SARIMAX
import warnings

# Define parameter ranges
qs = range(0, 3)  # Range for q
ps = range(0, 3)  # Range for p
d = 1             # Fixed value for d
parameters_list = list(product(ps, qs))  # Generate all combinations of p and q

# Initialize variables
results = []
best_aic = float("inf")  # Best AIC starts at infinity

warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')  # Ignore warnings during model fitting

# Model selection loop
for param in parameters_list:
    try:
        # Fit SARIMAX model
        model = SARIMAX(btc_month['close_box'], order=(param[0], d, param[1])).fit(disp=False)
        aic = model.aic  # Get AIC for the current model

        # Update best model if AIC improves
        if aic < best_aic:
            best_model = model
            best_aic = aic
            best_param = param

        # Store results
        results.append([param, aic])
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"Bad parameter combination {param}: {e}")
        continue

# Display the best model parameters and AIC
print(f"Best model: SARIMA{best_param}, AIC: {best_aic}")

Best model: SARIMA(1, 0), AIC: 38.85702944203104

# Inverse Box-Cox Transformation Function
def invboxcox(y,lmbda):
   if lmbda == 0:
      return(np.exp(y))
   else:
      return(np.exp(np.log(lmbda*y+1)/lmbda))

def invboxcox_manual(y, lmbda):
    if lmbda == 0:
        return np.exp(y)
    else:
        return np.power(y * lmbda + 1, 1 / lmbda)
In [125]:
# Ensure index is datetime
btc_month.index = pd.to_datetime(btc_month.index)

# Define start and end for prediction
start = btc_month.index[0]  # Start of the dataset
end = datetime(2018, 8, 31)  # Forecast horizon

# Manual invboxcox function
def invboxcox_manual(y, lmbda):
    if lmbda == 0:
        return np.exp(y)
    else:
        return np.power(y * lmbda + 1, 1 / lmbda)

# Forecasting
btc_month_pred = btc_month[['Close']].copy()
btc_month_pred['forecast'] = invboxcox_manual(best_model.predict(start=start, end=end), lmbda)

# Plot results
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
btc_month_pred['Close'].plot(label='Actual Close', linewidth=3)
btc_month_pred['forecast'].plot(label='Predicted Close', color='r', ls='--', linewidth=3)

plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.title('Bitcoin Monthly Forecast')
plt.ylabel('USD')
plt.show()

btc_month_predict = btc_month['2015-01-01':'2017-01-01']

# Get a naive forecast
close_history = [x for x in btc_month_predict['Close']]
predictions = list()
for i in range(len(btc_month_predict)):
    # predict
    predictions.append(close_history[-1])
    # update observation
    close_history.append(btc_month_predict.iloc[i]['Close'])
    
# Calculate RMSE
rmse = sqrt(mean_squared_error(btc_month_predict['Close'], predictions))
print('RMSE: %.2f' % rmse)

RMSE: 136.51

In [135]:
# Get the dynamic forecast between dates t1 and t2
t1 = pd.to_datetime('2017-06-30')
t2 = pd.to_datetime('2018-01-31')
btc_month_dynamic = best_model.get_prediction(start=t1, end=t2, dynamic=True, full_results=True)
btc_month_sarima['dynamic_forecast'] = invboxcox(btc_month_dynamic.predicted_mean, lmbda)

# Taking 80% confidence interval because the 95% blows out too high to visualise
pred_dynamic_ci = btc_month_dynamic.conf_int(alpha=0.2)
pred_dynamic_ci['lower close_box'] = invboxcox(pred_dynamic_ci['lower close_box'], lmbda)
pred_dynamic_ci['upper close_box'] = invboxcox(pred_dynamic_ci['upper close_box'], lmbda)

# Plot
plt.ylim((0,20000))

btc_month_sarima.Close['2016':'2018-01'].plot(label='close', linewidth=3)
btc_month_sarima.dynamic_forecast.plot(color='r', ls='--', label='dynamic forecast', linewidth=3)

plt.fill_between(pred_dynamic_ci.index,
                 pred_dynamic_ci.iloc[:, 0],
                pred_dynamic_ci.iloc[:, 1], color='k', alpha=.25)
plt.fill_betweenx(plt.ylim(), t1, t2, alpha=.1, zorder=-1)

plt.legend()
plt.title('Bitcoin Dynamic Monthly Forecast (backtesting)')
plt.grid()
plt.ylabel('USD')
